title: CHEMICAL PROCESS EQUIPMENT: SELECTION AND DESIGN
description: Author: James R. Couper, W. Roy Penney, PhD James R. Fair Edition: 3 edition Publication Date: December 6, 2012 Publisher: Butterworth-Heinemann Pages: 864 pages Format: pdf Size: 14M --- Chemical Process Equipment is a results-oriented reference for engineers who specify, design, maintain or run chemical and process plants. This book delivers information on the selection, sizing and operation of process equipment in a format that enables quick and accurate decision making on standard process and equipment choices, saving time, improving productivity, and building understanding. Coverage emphasizes common real-world equipment design rather than experimental or esoteric and focuses on maximizing performance. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/chemical-process-equipment-selection-and-design/
